description.narrative: (Kyrgyz Republic): The goal of this program is to help the Kyrgyz Republic further consolidate its democracy through strengthening the responsiveness and sustainability of political institutions - specifically political parties, elected parliamentary representatives, and election administration bodies. FY 2014 funds will be used to support the country's preparation for fall 2015 Parliamentary elections through training for political parties, civic education on election-related rights and obligations, support to the Central Election Commission and other electoral management bodies, and improved mechanisms for communication between elected officials and citizens.

Objectives for Kyrgyzstan: The Kyrgyzstan Political Processes Program is a four-year program funded by the United States Agency for International Development (USAID) and the United Kingdom Department for International Development (DFID). This program is implemented by all three members of the Consortium for Elections and Political Process Strengthening (CEPPS) and works to consolidate the Kyrgyzstan’s democratic path by supporting the development of a multi-party political system with strong, national parties, developing the next generation of leaders by equipping youth and women with the skills to actively engage in the political process and improving local government transparency and responsiveness.
